Rule Name: ai-test-generation
Description: Generate comprehensive tests when creating or modifying code. Use the appropriate test framework for the language.
Filters:
  - file: "*.py"
  - file: "*.js"
  - file: "*.ts"
  - file: "*.rs"
  - file: "*.go"
---
// TEST GENERATION GUIDE

## Test Coverage Requirements
- Unit tests for all new functions and methods
- Integration tests for API endpoints and database operations
- Edge case tests (empty input, invalid input, boundary values)
- Error path tests (exception handling, error states)

## Framework Per Language
- Python: pytest
- JavaScript/TypeScript: vitest or jest
- Rust: cargo test
- Go: go test

## Test Structure
```
// Unit test pattern
describe('function/component name', () => {
  it('should handle normal case', () => { ... })
  it('should handle edge case', () => { ... })
  it('should handle error case', () => { ... })
})
```

## Naming Convention
- test_[function_name]_[scenario]
- [function] should [expected behavior] when [condition]

## What to Test
1. Happy path: normal inputs produce expected outputs
2. Edge cases: empty/null/undefined inputs, max/min values
3. Error handling: invalid inputs, network failures, auth failures
4. State changes: verify side effects and state mutations
